metadata.name: Nishikigoi #112
metadata.description:
A calm exploration of generative koi ponds.
Infinitely procedurally animated.

Nishikigoi recreates the meditative experience of watching swimming koi. You may click to feed your koi fish, but only once every 30 minutes.

I hope you enjoy this little experience.

metadata.name: Wall of Chart #107
Dencity #955
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Primordial #220
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Pano #100
metadata.description:
'Pano' means ‘fabric’ in Portuguese.

This project is inspired by Bauhaus textile works, especially from the artists:
Ruth Hollos-Consemüller and Gunta Stolzl

15 color palettes
3 tile sizes
2 orientation
and two special features

You can read more about the process in my article on Fx(text)

metadata.name: Tessera #230
metadata.description:
Tessera is a project inspired by historical Mosaics. A tessera (Latin) is a small individual tile, usually formed in the shape of a square, used for making a mosaic. As the world's first "pixel art", Tessera is a tribute to this craft. This collection is made solely of rectangles on a two-dimensional canvas into an abstract mosaic flow with a three-dimensional effect.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Oktober 2022

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #293
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Boneyard #8
metadata.description:
The Boneyard on a cold, October evening is a foreboding place.  Each iteration has a unique arrangement of generative tombstones, a creepy rot-iron fence, dead trees and ghost orbs.  

Press the Down Arrow to save any frame as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.

Created using p5.js.

metadata.name: Wondering #165
metadata.description:
The work contains a fluid simulation. I put random forces into the simulation and let it run 500 steps to create a flow field and then use it to generate the visuals. 

I choose fluid simulation instead of curl noise or any other noise function because I believe the fluid simulation could generate a movement that's more dynamic and organic. The result is a combination of big and small vortices.


This piece requires WebGL2 to run, please check and make sure this runs on your device in advance. Also you can press the spacebar to toggle the camera control.
